1 Introduction
**************

The ‘howm-todo’ package provides cross-compatible TODO prioritization
that works in both Howm (https://kaorahi.github.io/howm/) notes and in
Org-mode files.  Org-mode picks up the literal keyword ‘TODO’ in its
agenda views, and Howm leaves the line alone, so a single marker form
serves both tools.

   The marker takes the form ‘TODO [XY]’.  ‘X’ is an uppercase letter
that names a priority group.  ‘Y’ is a non-negative integer that ranks
the item inside the group.  A larger ‘Y’ means lower priority, so ‘[A1]’
outranks ‘[A2]’ which outranks ‘[A44]’ which outranks ‘[B1]’.

   The package supports three workflows.

  1. Selecting a region of manually ordered items and adding ‘TODO [XY]’
     markers across them.  Blank lines separate priority groups.

  2. Sorting an already-marked region by ‘[XY]’ priority.

  3. Stripping markers from a region so the items can be re-prioritized
     the next day.

   A fourth workflow attaches an Org-style ‘:project:’ tag to a marked
line by reading project names from a SQLite database the user maintains
for time tracking.


