2 Installation
**************

2.1 Manual install with the Makefile
====================================

The simplest path is to clone or copy the source tree and run:

     make compile
     make info
     sudo make install

By default the package installs into
‘/usr/local/share/emacs/site-lisp/howm-todo’ and the info file installs
into ‘/usr/local/share/info’.  Override ‘PREFIX’, ‘ELISPDIR’, or
‘INFODIR’ on the command line to install elsewhere.

     make install PREFIX=$HOME/.local

   After install, add the install directory to ‘load-path’ and call
‘require’:

     (add-to-list 'load-path "/usr/local/share/emacs/site-lisp/howm-todo")
     (require 'howm-todo)

2.2 straight.el
===============

     (straight-use-package
      '(howm-todo :type git
                  :host github
                  :repo "blaine-mooers/howm-todo"))

2.3 use-package with straight
=============================

     (use-package howm-todo
       :straight (howm-todo :type git
                            :host github
                            :repo "blaine-mooers/howm-todo")
       :commands (howm-todo-prioritize-region
                  howm-todo-strip-region
                  howm-todo-sort-region
                  howm-todo-add-project-tag
                  howm-todo-tag-region)
       :custom
       (howm-todo-db-path "~/60003TimeTracking/cb/tenKprojects.db"))


