3 Concepts
**********

A “priority cookie” is the bracketed text ‘[XY]’ that follows the ‘TODO’
keyword.

‘X’, the “group letter”
     A single uppercase letter from ‘A’ through ‘Z’.  Groups model
     coarse priority bands.  ‘A’ is the most urgent.

‘Y’, the “rank”
     A non-negative integer.  Smaller is higher priority.  ‘Y’ may have
     one or more digits.  The package sorts numerically, so ‘C2’
     outranks ‘C10’ which outranks ‘C100’.

   The “project tag” is an Org-style ‘:tag:’ block appended to the end
of a marked line.  When the line already ends with one or more
‘:foo:bar:’ tags, the new tag is merged into that block as
‘:foo:bar:new:’ rather than starting a second block.


