4 Commands
**********

 -- Command: howm-todo-prioritize-region beg end
     Add ‘TODO [XY]’ prefixes to every non-empty line in the region
     between BEG and END.  Blank lines separate priority groups, so the
     first contiguous block of non-empty lines is labeled ‘A1’, ‘A2’,
     ‘A3’, the second block becomes ‘B1’, ‘B2’, and so on.  Any
     pre-existing ‘TODO [XY]’ markers in the region are stripped first,
     so the command is idempotent and safe to run more than once.
     Leading whitespace on each line is preserved.

 -- Command: howm-todo-strip-region beg end
     Remove every ‘TODO [XY]’ marker from each line between BEG and END.
     Leading whitespace is preserved.  Use this command before
     re-prioritizing items the next day.

 -- Command: howm-todo-sort-region beg end
     Sort the lines between BEG and END by their ‘TODO [XY]’ priority.
     Lines that have no marker sink to the end of the region and keep
     their original relative order.  The sort is stable among lines that
     share the same priority cookie.

 -- Command: howm-todo-add-project-tag
     Append an Org-style ‘:project:’ tag to the end of the current
     ‘TODO’ line.  The project name is read from the SQLite database
     referenced by ‘howm-todo-db-path’ through ‘completing-read’.  When
     the line already ends with a ‘:foo:bar:’ block, the new tag is
     merged into that block.  When the project tag is already present,
     the command is a no-op.  Signals an error when the current line has
     no ‘TODO [XY]’ marker.

 -- Command: howm-todo-tag-region beg end
     Walk every line between BEG and END and call
     ‘howm-todo-add-project-tag’ on each line that carries a ‘TODO [XY]’
     marker.  Unmarked lines are skipped.


