5 Customization
***************

 -- User Option: howm-todo-db-path
     Absolute path to the SQLite database that holds project metadata.

     Default: ‘~/60003TimeTracking/cb/tenKprojects.db’.

 -- User Option: howm-todo-db-table
     Table in the database that holds the project rows.  When ‘nil’,
     ‘howm-todo’ inspects every table in the database and picks the
     first one whose schema includes a column named by
     ‘howm-todo-db-column’.

     Default: ‘nil’ (auto-detect).

 -- User Option: howm-todo-db-column
     Column name to read project names from.

     Default: ‘"ProjectDirectory"’.

 -- User Option: howm-todo-keyword
     Leading keyword on a prioritized line.  Both Howm and Org-mode
     recognize the literal text ‘TODO’ at the start of a line.  Changing
     this value lets you adopt a different word without modifying the
     package.

     Default: ‘"TODO"’.

 -- User Option: howm-todo-tag-use-basename
     When non-‘nil’, the Org tag is built from the basename of the
     project path returned by the database.  When ‘nil’, the full path
     is sanitized into a tag.

     Default: ‘t’.


