6 SQLite Project Database
*************************

The package prefers the built-in ‘sqlite’ library shipped with Emacs 29
or newer compiled with ‘--with-sqlite3’.  When the built-in library is
unavailable, the package falls back to the ‘sqlite3’ command-line shell.
Either backend is enough.

   The default expected schema looks like:

     CREATE TABLE projects (
         id               INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
         ProjectDirectory TEXT
     );

The table name is not significant when ‘howm-todo-db-table’ is ‘nil’;
the package detects whichever table contains the ‘ProjectDirectory’
column.  If you keep your projects in a different column, set
‘howm-todo-db-column’.  If multiple tables contain that column, set
‘howm-todo-db-table’ explicitly to pin detection.

   Project names are de-duplicated and sorted before they are presented
to ‘completing-read’, so the picker is consistent regardless of how many
duplicate rows you have in the table.


